data.content:
Here's the minimal program (`Program.cs`):

```csharp
using System.Text.Json;

var options = new JsonSerializerOptions { PropertyNamingPolicy = JsonNamingPolicy.CamelCase };
var json = JsonSerializer.Serialize(new Person("Jane", 30), options);
Console.WriteLine(json);

public record Person(string Name, int Age);
```

Output: `{"name":"Jane","age":30}` ✓

The key is `JsonNamingPolicy.CamelCase` passed via `JsonSerializerOptions` — no extra NuGet packages needed since `System.Text.Json` is built into .NET 8. The record declaration goes after the top-level statements (C# requirement).
